Sentencas: We evaluated the performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with a 50 nm thin silver (Ag) cathode surface treated with cerium oxide (CeOx) by atomic layer deposition (ALD).
Titulo: Nanoporous silver cathode surface treated by atomic layer deposition of CeOx for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performances of bare and ALD-treated Ag cathodes were evaluated on gadolinia-doped ceria (GDC) electrolyte supporting cells with a platinum (Pt) anode over 300 degrees C- 450 degrees C.
Titulo: Nanoporous silver cathode surface treated by atomic layer deposition of CeOx for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our work confirms that ALD CeOx treatment enhances cathodic performance and thermal stability of the Ag cathode.
Titulo: Nanoporous silver cathode surface treated by atomic layer deposition of CeOx for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The performance difference between cells using a Ag cathode optimally treated with an ALD CeOx surface and a reference Pt cathode is about 50% at 450 degrees C in terms of fuel cell power output in our experiment.
Titulo: Nanoporous silver cathode surface treated by atomic layer deposition of CeOx for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The bare Ag cathode completely agglomerated into islands during fuel cell operation at 450 degrees C, while the ALD CeOx treatment effectively protects the porosity of the cathode.
Titulo: Nanoporous silver cathode surface treated by atomic layer deposition of CeOx for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: We also discuss the long-term stability of ALD CeOx-treated Ag cathodes related to the microstructure of the layers.
Titulo: Nanoporous silver cathode surface treated by atomic layer deposition of CeOx for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
